-- SAIC wins $1.05 bln Pentagon supply order
-- 
-- Mon Sep 17, 2007 5:39pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/17/us-saic-pentagon-idUSN1735939720070917

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Science Applications International Corp SAI.N has won a one-year contract valued at up to $1.05 billion to provide maintenance, repair and operations supplies to the Army, Air Force, Navy and Marine Corps, the Pentagon said on Monday. 

 This marked the third option year under SAIC's contract with the Defense Logistics Agency, the Pentagon said in its daily listing of defense contracts. It said the deal has indefinite delivery and indefinite quantity terms, allowing the services and federal civilian agencies to order supplies from SAIC. (Reporting by  Andrea Shalal-Esa )